First Lady Melania Trump celebrated the one year anniversary of her BE BEST campaign, which focuses on children's well-being, online safety, and opioid abuse. She announced the expansion of the campaign to include a focus on online safety and children of all ages affected by opioid abuse. She also announced the appointment of a BE BEST Ambassador through the United States Agency for International Development and a second solo international tour. The First Lady recognized the Farming High School Robotics Team for designing a motorized wheelchair for a 5-year-old boy with limited mobility. She expressed gratitude to partner agencies and organizations that have supported her initiative and called for the appointment of BE BEST Ambassadors within all partner agencies. The First Lady emphasized the importance of promoting character education programs, safe online behaviors, and addressing drug addiction. She pledged to continue visiting schools, hospitals, and organizations to promote BE BEST and engage with children.